X\subsection{Torus Parameter Editing}
X
XThe TOR general class of solids contains only one type of torus, one with
Xcircular cross-sections.
XThe defining parameters of the TOR are two radii (r1 and r2), a normal
Xvector (N), and the vertex (V).
XThe scalar r1 is the distance from the vertex to the midpoint of the
Xcircular cross section.
XThe scalar r2 is the radius of the circular cross-section.
XThe vector N is used to orient the torus.
XDuring solid editing, none of these parameters are labeled on the screen.
XFigure \ref{ped-tor} depicts a typical torus during parameter editing.
X
XThe parameter editing of the TOR consists of scaling the radii, hence the
Xmenu contains only two members.
